Summary - Theory & Concept of the Ecological Niche
1. The Niche Width expressed by individual morphs in the whole population:
. Within-phenotype component: High - Few mono/oligo-morph generalists
. Between-phenotype component: High - Many poly-morph specialists.
2. The general relationship between Niche Overlap and Competition:
. Intraspecific: Population density1 > Degree of generalists > Niche width 1
. Interspecific: Species density1 > Degree of specialists1 > Niche width
3. There are 4 modes of interspecies niche relationship and positioning:
. Included: The included is inferior and will eventually be excluded
. Disjunct: Niches are clearly separated and no competition exist
. Abutting: Niches adjacent with minimal competition (contiguous allopatry).
. Overlapping: Niches may overlap more than the maximum for coexistence
4. Basic Rules for niche width, niche overlap and limiting similarity
